25 I have placed before you: now feed yourself with it;
26 because to itself turns all my care
27 that matter from which I am made a scribe.

28 The greatest minister of nature, 29 that with the value of heaven imprints the world 30 and with its light measures the time,
31 with that part which above is remembered 32 joined, was turning through the spirals 33 in which more readily always it appears;
