query.result:
70 In the court of heaven, from which I return,
71 are found many joys dear and beautiful
72 so that they cannot be drawn from the kingdom;

73 and the song of those lights was of those;
74 whoever does not take wing so that up there he flies,
75 let him await from the mute ones then the news.

82 And within one heard begin: “When 83 the ray of grace, with which true love is kindled 84 and that then grows loving,
85 multiplied in you so much resplends, 86 that it leads you up by that ladder 87 where without ascending no one descends;
88 whoever denied you the wine from his vial 89 for your thirst, would not be in freedom 90 if not like water that does not fall to the sea.”
